Harp and fiddle is a traditional Irish dive bar with traditional Irish bar food.  We went on a Saturday night and it was live music to boot!  The food was really good I especially like the beef stew and the meat pies.  If you're a fan of Irish coffee I heartily recommend it. Because it's Bethesda parking is wretched, and I recommend using one of the public lots and hopefully you will get a spot.  The good news is that it's free on the weekends. The wait staff was a lot of fun and would go right to the kitchen or the bar if you needed anything that they were unsure of.  they were also very attentive when it came to refilling a glass or clearing a table. Information, this is a great place to spend a few hours here great music eat some good food in a place that is really good for what it is - a really nice Irish dive bar with live music!

I have visited this pub three times, so far. The Guinness (an easy choice) is on tap and tastes as it should. My friend's Jameson was a healthy pour. Food was properly pub-like, with curry fries and brown gravy, mini meat pies, and an Irish BLT rounding out our order.  The occasional loud drunk is part of the charm of dining in a bar, so no worries there. Just be aware that it's not the sort of "family" place one might bring children and expect 100% decorum. Maybe 80%? Still, I'd leave the kids home, at night.  Let's not forget the live music! I haven't actually experienced that yet, so no critique; but it does exist, some nights.  Worth returning to? Yes. Perhaps next weekend...

Desiring dinner and a few drinks we quickly understood that substandard service is was what we were in store for. So we took our business elsewhere down to Rock bottom. We had a great meal, great service, and great atmosphere...and that is where my family, friends and I will be spending our leisure hours from now on. I was simply very disappointed with Flanagan's Harp & fiddle and expected much more from such great reviews. It makes me wonder who wrote those reviews now. Maybe the bartender, waitress, owners and their family members. Because I didn't see a 4.7 when I walked in!

Very disappointing ordering experience. After a late work day, wife was craving a burger so we ordered delivery. She ordered the Belfast Dinner Burger and I ordered the Shepards' pie. Food arrived and it looked fine, although my pie being served in a clear, plastic food storage container was a bit off-putting. However, real trouble came when my wife bit into her burger.  She's a bit of a germophobe and always gets her burgers well-done, this burger however was rare on the first bite. Disgusted, she cut the burger in half, and it was rblue (raw) at the center. I tried to recook the patty for her but the experience had ruined her appetite.

What a disappointment. Went for a girls night out to have dinner at 6pm and hear music which website said it began at 8:30pm. It didnt. Band arrived well after 9:30pm to just start setting up. We opted to sit at a table so omw could talk instead of at bar.  Table Service was atrocious and nonexistent. Place was very empty. We were here 3+ hours. Several staff members on duty, all couldn't care less to help unless you were seated at the bar . Not one offer to refill our water or come to table. Only time someone came to table was to drop off a menu 20 minutes after being seated. We literally were ignored sitting at tables. Noone waits on tables, just stand in bar and goof off . We had to go to bar to get everything...dinner, beer, etc. Plenty of other Irish pubs that you can visit for a better evening out. None of us would come back here.

Wow! FRAUD ALERT!! Charged more on my card than authorized!  Patrons BEWARE!!  Keep all your receipts because they'll charge you what they feel is right!  WRONG!!!!  Friends and I went to see the 6 Nations rugby tournament on Sat morning, had a few beverages and a bite of breakfast, which was good.  Sadly, they did not disclose a $20 per person cover charge for the game viewing.  Just "a cover".  Then after giving us a single bill for the three of us, we divided it ourselves and each paid.  Two with cash and myself with my visa.  Only to find they charged me more on my card when my bank posts the charge!  That's FRAUD!  I did not authorize a higher amount than on my receipt.  And I still have it.  So, lesson learned: don't pay or visit with a credit card at FLANAGAN's !!!

Their food was delicious but they attempted to add the gratuity to the bill without disclosing that in writing and in advance before ordering the food. It is my opinion that practice is dishonest and deceptive. They did correct the bill but I shouldn't have had to do that. I have no issue with tipping but the customer does not have to give a gratuity and it's a privilege to have a tip. That was disclosed nowhere on the menu or anywhere conspicuous in the establishment. I don't care how good the food is; DISHONEST business practices give you an automatic ZERO.

A friend had a small celebration there. We went on a Wednesday night and I was glad I had a parking spot outside in no time. They had Karaoke night and therefore a mixed crowd of people was present. It is a regular bar with regular people and that made me feel like I am a regular there, even so that was my 1st time. My friend had food catered. It was blue-cheese filled tomatoes, salad chicken wraps, salmon creme on cucumber, peppers filled with bacon and cheese which was my favorite. Everything tasted good and the service was outstanding. They do have a small outdoor area in between the buildings which I would have liked but everyone was smoking there. I had a great time I guess that deserves 5 stars.

Flanagans is OK but I think it could be better.  The beer selection is fine, the furniture is fine, the recipes could be spruced up, some different lighting would probably improve the decor in front around the bar, but the most important thing they could do is stop having bands play there.  It gets too loud inside and is just obnoxious.  If they were folk bands it would be ok but they aren't.  It's a fine place to have a couple drinks during the day, afternoon, and early evening, but I'd leave before the bands start.

I had the most expensive Sheppards pie, and it was like eating soup. My wife had corned beef and cabbage, no taste what so ever, again expensive. They doubled the price on the menu because of St. Patrick's day. Don't go out of your way for this place. Be sure to keep a copy of your receipt and make sure they charge you the right price including tip, our waitress tipped herself and extra 4 bucks. I wasn't drunk enough to slip that past me and the bland food. I can make better pie, and corned beef and cabbage at home. I gave them two stars because the beer was cold and not made by them.
